   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>28 8.6.8.6.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Joined to the Christ victorious,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>And workings of His cross,</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>I'm nourished e'en in sufferings,</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>And safe in any loss.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Joined to the Christ, the risen One,</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Ascended into heav'n;</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>In light of the eternal cross,</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Unbounded grace is giv'n.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Joined to the Christ victorious,</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>My spirit's joys increase;</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>I call the holy, highest name,</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>And Satan's powers cease.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Joined to the Christ, the sovereign One,</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To Him I long to cling.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>His cross has spoiled the serpent's work,</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Of vict'ry now I sing.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Joined to the Christ how marvelous!</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>God's great salvation this!</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>"The Lamb is worthy," well we sing,</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>All praise and power His.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>29 8.8.8.8.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Hymns, #488</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Lord, Thou hast shown the mystery,</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>How on the Cross I died with Thee;</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>I need no other pow'r or way</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>That I may triumph day by day.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>That cross of Thine is also mine,</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Into my life its light doth shine;</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>When I believe I'm dead with Thee,</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>The world has lost its pow'r o'er me.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Since I am crucified with Thee,</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>From sin and self I am set free;</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>How can I still enjoy the world</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Or seek its vanities unfurled?</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>I take my place, dear Lord, with Thee</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Upon the cross of Calvary.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Thy life and power then are mine,</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Since Thou and I in oneness twine.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Since Thou didst come to slay the foe,</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>His work and power to overthrow,</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>I too can overcome in Thee</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>And prove Thy mighty pow'r in me.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Yet, for the vict'ry we rely</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Upon the death which Thou didst die;</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>We tread the path which Thou hast trod</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>Until we reach the goal in God.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>My death with Thee I now believe</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>And all its meaning would receive.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>Thy death more deeply show to me,</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>That from my flesh I may be free.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>I long to win as Thou hast won,</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>To reign with Thee when Thou dost come.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>If we the cross will gladly bear,</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Then in Thy glory we will share.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
